00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:02,660
So once you know you tested positive,

200
00:11:02,660 --> 00:11:06,090
you're on one of those branches, which of
those is actually having cellulite?

201
00:11:06,090 --> 00:11:07,380
Only the top branch.

202
00:11:07,380 --> 00:11:11,065
So the probability that you're actually
going to get the disease,

203
00:11:11,065 --> 00:11:13,611
given that you tested positive in this
case,

204
00:11:13,611 --> 00:11:19,500
will be .546 divided by .259, plus .546,
and that again, comes out to be 67.8%.

205
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,420
So you can solve it

206
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:23,090
this way if you're more comfortable still
with the tree, and Bayes' Rule.

207
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:26,513
And I'm going to show you even one more
